And still on the 2020 KCPEresults announced today, candidates with special needs have recorded an improvement in the overall marks compared to the year 2019 where the top candidate scored 414 marks out of the possible 500 marks.&nbsp;Education cabinet secretary lauded the increase that saw this years candidate score 420 marks out of the possible 500 adding that the improvement only means that candidates with special needs can stillexcel in national examinations if given a fair and conducive environment